cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with dense correspondences between RGB images and a surface-based representation of the human body, which is a core topic in computer vision. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions training CNN-based systems and an inpainting network to improve the effectiveness of the training set. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing a system that can estimate human pose in the wild, which involves AI techniques such as object recognition and image segmentation. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with processing images and videos to estimate human pose. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on creating or rendering graphics, but rather on estimating human pose from images.
